# Test Case Set — 6753 — Subclaim Snapshot JSON Field Creation

## Metadata
- Case ID: 6753
- Source Artifact: Jira Story 6753 — Create subclaim snapshot JSON fields for IPRs
- Agent Used: Test Case Generator
- Test Author: Adam Musinski
- Date Created: 2026-03-23
- Scope: Validation of creation, visibility, immutability, and update behavior of the subclaim snapshot JSON field on IPRs via front-end actions and the Django Admin IPR Detail View.
- Out of Scope: Backfill of historical IPR data. Performance improvements. Use of snapshot data for calculations. Follow-on tickets addressing backfill and calculation usage.

---
## Objective
Validate that the system consistently creates, displays, protects, and updates a subclaim snapshot JSON field on IPRs in response to defined front-end events, and that the snapshot data observable in the Django Admin IPR Detail View accurately reflects the most recent triggering action.

---
## Preconditions
- System is deployed to a testable environment.
- Monitoring and observability tooling is enabled.
- Internal users authenticate via SSO.
- User has permitted access to the Django Admin IPR Detail View.
- Front-end workflows for generating IPRs and modifying subclaims are available.

---
## Assumptions & Constraints
- Snapshot creation is triggered only by the front-end events explicitly defined in the acceptance criteria.
- Functional behavior outside snapshot creation and storage is unchanged.
- Snapshot data structure and internal calculations are not validated, only observable presence and overwrite behavior.

---
## Acceptance Criteria (Derived)
| AC ID | Description |
|-----|-------------|
| AC-1 | A new subclaim snapshot JSON field exists on all IPRs. |
| AC-2 | The snapshot JSON field is visible on the Django Admin IPR Detail View and is read-only for all users, including superusers. |
| AC-3 | A snapshot of subclaim data is saved when specific front-end events occur. |
| AC-4 | New snapshot data overwrites any existing snapshot data on the IPR. |

---
## Manual Test Cases
| Test Case ID | Title | Type | Preconditions | Steps | Expected Result |
|------------|-------|------|---------------|-------|-----------------|
| 6753-TC-001 | Snapshot field exists on IPR | Functional | Internal SSO user has access to Django Admin IPR Detail View. At least one IPR exists. | 1. Navigate to an existing IPR in Django Admin.<br>2. Scroll through available fields.<br>3. Locate the subclaim snapshot JSON field. | The subclaim snapshot JSON field is present and visible on the IPR detail view. |
| 6753-TC-002 | Snapshot field is read-only | Functional | Internal SSO user has access to Django Admin IPR Detail View. IPR has snapshot data. | 1. Open an existing IPR in Django Admin.<br>2. Attempt to edit the snapshot JSON field.<br>3. Attempt to save the IPR. | The snapshot JSON field does not allow editing. No changes are saved. |
| 6753-TC-003 | Snapshot field is read-only for superuser | Negative | Internal superuser has access to Django Admin IPR Detail View. IPR has snapshot data. | 1. Open an existing IPR as superuser.<br>2. Attempt to modify snapshot JSON field.<br>3. Save the IPR. | The snapshot JSON field remains unchanged and read-only for superuser. |
| 6753-TC-004 | Snapshot created on IPR generation | Functional | User can generate IPRs via front end. | 1. Generate a new IPR via front end.<br>2. Open the IPR in Django Admin.<br>3. View snapshot JSON field. | Snapshot JSON field is populated with subclaim data from the generation event. |
| 6753-TC-005 | Snapshot updated when subclaims are removed | Functional | IPR exists with subclaims and snapshot data. | 1. Remove one or more subclaims via front end.<br>2. Open IPR in Django Admin.<br>3. View snapshot JSON field. | Snapshot JSON reflects subclaim removal. |
| 6753-TC-006 | Snapshot updated when subclaims moved to Submitted | Functional | IPR exists with subclaims not in Submitted state. | 1. Move subclaims to Submitted via front end.<br>2. Open IPR in Django Admin.<br>3. View snapshot JSON field. | Snapshot JSON reflects Submitted state. |
| 6753-TC-007 | Snapshot updated when subclaims moved to Unsubmitted | Functional | IPR exists with subclaims in Submitted state. | 1. Move subclaims to Unsubmitted via front end.<br>2. Open IPR in Django Admin.<br>3. View snapshot JSON field. | Snapshot JSON reflects Unsubmitted state. |
| 6753-TC-008 | Snapshot overwrites existing data | Edge Case | IPR exists with existing snapshot data. | 1. Record current snapshot JSON value.<br>2. Trigger a snapshot-generating front-end action.<br>3. Refresh IPR in Django Admin. | Snapshot JSON contains new data and previous snapshot data is fully overwritten. |

---
## Observability Validation Notes
- No new error or warning alerts are generated during snapshot creation or overwrite.
- No timeout or recalculation-related error events occur.
- Only expected informational logs are present for snapshot save events.

---
## Risks & Edge Considerations
- Snapshot may not trigger if front-end events are bypassed.
- Partial snapshot overwrite could lead to stale data if not fully replaced.
- Environment latency could delay visibility of updated snapshot data.

